thread.title: Aust dollar higher ahead of Fed decision
thread.title_full: Aust dollar higher ahead of Fed decision | Business Spectator

author: AAP
title: Aust dollar higher ahead of Fed decision
text:
The Australian dollar has managed to stay above US71c as traders sit on the sidelines awaiting the much anticipated US interest rate decision.
At 12.00pm (AEST) on Wednesday, the currency was trading at US71.34c, up from US71.15c on Tuesday.
During the morning, it traded between US71.23c and US71.46c.
There is a one-in-three chance the Federal Reserve will announce a rate rise early on Friday morning (AEST), and one is fully priced in for some time by January.
